LAKSHMI CHAND KHAJURIA & ORS V. SMT. ISHROO DEVI [1977] INSC 100; AIR 1977 SC 1694; 1977 (3) SCR 400; 1977 (2) SCC 501 (31 March 1977)

 KAILASAM, P.S.
 KAILASAM, P.S.
 GUPTA, A.C.
 
CITATION: 1977 AIR 1694 1977 SCR (3) 400 1977 SCC (2) 501 
ACT:
 Testamentary Will disposing of the ancestral property to a far relation, whether valid under s. 27 of the Jammu & Kashmir Hindu Succession Act, 1956--Scope of s. 27 and explanation thereto--Whether income of a hereditary priest, a hereditary Property--Mitakshara law as applicable to Jammu & Kashmir--Though a wife cannot demand a partition she is entitled to receive a share equal to that of a son and to hold and enjoy that share separately even from her husband.
 
